1. Employee Salary Calculation System
Problem Statement
A company wants to calculate salaries for different types of employees.
1.	Create an abstract class Employee containing:
o	empId
o	name
o	Abstract method calculateSalary()
o	Concrete method displayEmployee() to show employee details.
2.	Create two subclasses:
o	FullTimeEmployee
o	ContractEmployee
3.	Salary rules:
o	FullTimeEmployee → salary = basic + HRA + allowance
o	ContractEmployee → salary = hoursWorked × ratePerHour
4.	Demonstrate the functionality in the main class.
2. Online Shopping Discount System
Problem Statement
Design a Discount System for an E-commerce platform.
1.	Create an interface Discount with method:
o	calculateDiscount(double price)
2.	Implement this interface in:
o	FestivalDiscount
o	SeasonalDiscount
3.	Each class should calculate discount differently.
Example:
•	Festival → 20%
•	Seasonal → 10%
4.	Display the final price after discount.
Vehicle Rental System (Interface Based Design)
Problem Statement
A vehicle rental company wants to build a system to manage rentals for different types of vehicles such as cars and bikes. The rental charge calculation differs depending on the vehicle type.
1.	Create an interface Rental with the following methods:
o	rentVehicle(int days)
o	calculateRent(int days)
o	displayDetails()
2.	Implement this interface in two classes:
o	Car
o	Bike
3.	Each class should contain the following attributes:
o	vehicleId
o	vehicleName
o	rentPerDay
4.	Rental calculation rules:
o	Car
	Rent = days × rentPerDay
	If days > 5, give 10% discount on total rent.
o	Bike
	Rent = days × rentPerDay
	If days > 3, give 5% discount on total rent.
5.	In the main class:
o	Create objects for Car and Bike.
o	Call rentVehicle() for different number of days.
o	Display vehicle details and the final rent amount.
